Global Cemented Carbide Mould Market Insights
Cemented Carbide Mould Market size was valued at USD 1.8 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 3.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Cemented Carbide Mould Market Overview
The global Cemented Carbide Mould Market is poised for significant growth, driven by expanding industries such as automotive, aerospace, and electronics. The market size was valued at approximately USD 3.5 billion in 2024 and is expected to reach USD 5.7 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.2% during the forecast period. The demand for cemented carbide moulds is escalating due to their exceptional hardness, wear resistance, and ability to withstand high temperatures, making them ideal for precision manufacturing. Technological advancements in material science and the increasing use of automated manufacturing processes also contribute to the growth trajectory of the market. The Asia-Pacific region, particularly China and India, are leading contributors to this growth, owing to the rapid industrialization and growth of key manufacturing sectors.

